## Project-specific rules

If you have conventions that apply ONLY to this project, write them as
rules and scope them to this directory:

```yaml
---
applies-to: ["~/projects/[this-project]/**"]
---

# Project-Specific Rule
...
```

Drop them in `~/.claude/rules/` — they'll only load when you're working
in this project. For conventions that apply across all your projects,
write the rule unscoped (loads globally) and store it in
`~/.claude/rules/` directly.
